<paragraph id="B84D36D59904FFF9FCC541991CF6FB01" blockId="21.[826,1441,898,1196]" pageId="21" pageNumber="316">
<emphasis id="8A86EAC79904FFF9FCC541991CC9FC35" box="[826,945,899,920]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="316">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
A 
<taxonomicName id="7FF24D569904FFF9FC1D41981B1AFC3A" box="[994,1122,898,919]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Pachycerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8A86EAC79904FFF9FC1D41981B1AFC3A" box="[994,1122,898,919]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="316">Pachycerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of large size, apparently related to 
<taxonomicName id="7FF24D569904FFF9FC4A41B81B60FC1A" baseAuthorityName="Germar" baseAuthorityYear="1824" box="[949,1048,930,951]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Pachycerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="segnis">
<emphasis id="8A86EAC79904FFF9FC4A41B81B60FC1A" box="[949,1048,930,951]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="316">P. segnis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is characterized by the scales being bifid, and only connate at the base, with very divergent teeth, regularly covering the whole integument, by the relatively long rostrum, with sharp, narrow, slightly converging dorsolateral keels, a broad median elevation, and a narrow median keel, by the elytra with spaced small glossy granules on the intervals, and by the shape of sternite VIII of the female.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B84D36D59904FFF9FCC546CF1B17FA29" blockId="21.[826,1442,1237,1412]" pageId="21" pageNumber="316">
